===Ask Chartonus about Nympha's whereabouts{{subst:void|<!--500040704-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=adventure|location="Eternal Holy City" Okhema|update|Times of trouble are what friends are for! Aelius decides to ask the helpful shopkeepers in the market, in the hopes of piecing together a clue from the fragmentary information they can offer.}}
{{Dialogue Start}}

;(Talk to Chartonus)
:'''Chartonus:''' What do you need, warrior of the outlands?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Nympha. Got any clues about her?
:'''Chartonus:''' Nympha, I'm so sorry. There was a lot, going on, and she was really upset.
:'''Chartonus:''' There was something weird... Chains... Nympha's butler, last week, ordered some chains.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Perhaps they were for tying her up?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} You Okhemans really know how to play hardball...
:'''Aelius:''' I've got a bad feeling about this, too... Chartonus, did they tell you where this stuff was going?
:'''Chartonus:''' They came by, picked it up, already gone. Really weird. In the past, always delivered things, to their house.
:'''Aelius:''' I see... If her family puts in any more orders with you, please let me know, my friend.
:'''Aelius:''' Go and ask Chartonus at the blacksmith shop. Maybe Nympha mentioned something to him before.
{{Dialogue End}}

