===Ask Theodoros about Nympha's whereabouts{{subst:void|<!--500040706-->}}===
{{Dialogue Start}}

;(Talk to Theodoros)
:'''Theodoros:''' Hand-painted pots and ancient artifacts, all at reasonable prices. Feel free to take a look around.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Nympha. Got any clues about her?
:'''Theodoros:''' Those depraved old aristocrats are stealing even their children's happiness. Remembering history makes us wise, but also repeats the cycle of tragedy.
:'''Theodoros:''' A few days back, I had a really suspicious trade &mdash; this guy who looked like a retainer wanting to pawn a priceless pendant made of Kremnos eagleblood.
:'''Theodoros:''' Eagleblood is very rare, and the rare extant treasures are mostly safeguarded by Kremnoans, so there's no way it'd be in the hands of an ordinary Okheman guard.
:'''Theodoros:''' When I hit him up about it, he just said some aristocrat in the city gifted it to him. Here, let me show you...
:'''Aelius:''' ...This!? That's my mother's eagleblood pendant that I gave to Nympha. I was worried about us getting busted, so I never let Nympha wear it. She must have hidden it very well somewhere at home.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} What's it doing here?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is that what Nympha wanted?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Someone found this pendant...
:'''Aelius:''' Every clue so far today points to one outcome and one alone: Nympha's family put her under duress.
:'''Theodoros:''' I kept a close eye on this bizarre customer. My friend said this guy has been hanging around {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|Marmoreal Palace}} a lot lately.
:'''Theodoros:''' Go, now! I hope this eagleblood can help lead you to the one you love.
:'''Aelius:''' Lastly, try asking Theodoros in the ancient artifacts store. Maybe there will be a clue or two in their recent transactions.
{{Dialogue End}}

